# Trivy CVE suppression file.
#
# Each line is one CVE id. Trivy excludes these from the report, so they will NOT
# fail the build. Use sparingly and ALWAYS document why a CVE is suppressed.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # Reason for suppression. Expiration: YYYY-MM-DD.
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2024-12345  # False positive in eclipse-temurin alpine layer. Re-evaluate 2026-12-01.
#
# Anything CRITICAL/HIGH that Trivy finds is blocking by default unless listed below.

# (No active suppressions.)
#
# CVE-2026-22732 (spring-security-web bypass) was previously suppressed while the
# project was pinned to Spring Boot 3.4.x (spring-security 6.4.13, unpatched). The
# bump to Spring Boot 3.5.14 ships spring-security-web 6.5.10 (>= the 6.5.9 fix), so
# the vulnerability is resolved at the source and the suppression has been removed.
# A clean-room Trivy image scan (--severity CRITICAL,HIGH --ignore-unfixed, NO
# ignorefile) of the 3.5.14 bootJar reports 0 findings, confirming nothing else
# needs suppressing.
